32/* DCU Transmit Filter macros */
33#define CALC_MMR(dcu, idx) \
34 ( (4 * dcu) + (idx < 32 ? 0 : (idx < 64 ? 1 : (idx < 96 ? 2 : 3))) )
35#define TXBLK_FROM_MMR(mmr) \
36 (AR_D_TXBLK_BASE + ((mmr & 0x1f) << 6) + ((mmr & 0x20) >> 3))
37#define CALC_TXBLK_ADDR(dcu, idx) (TXBLK_FROM_MMR(CALC_MMR(dcu, idx)))
38#define CALC_TXBLK_VALUE(idx) (1 << (idx & 0x1f))
39
40/* MAC register values */
41
42#define INIT_INTERRUPT_MASK \
43 ( AR_IMR_TXERR | AR_IMR_TXOK | AR_IMR_RXORN | \
44 AR_IMR_RXERR | AR_IMR_RXOK | AR_IMR_TXURN | \
45 AR_IMR_HIUERR )
46#define INIT_BEACON_CONTROL \
47 ( (INIT_RESET_TSF << 24) | (INIT_BEACON_EN << 23) | \
48 (INIT_TIM_OFFSET << 16) | INIT_BEACON_PERIOD )
49
50#define INIT_CONFIG_STATUS 0x00000000
51#define INIT_RSSI_THR 0x00000700 /* Missed beacon counter initialized to 0x7 (max is 0xff) */
52#define INIT_IQCAL_LOG_COUNT_MAX 0xF
53#define INIT_BCON_CNTRL_REG 0x00000000
54
55#define INIT_BEACON_PERIOD 0xffff
56#define INIT_TIM_OFFSET 0
57#define INIT_BEACON_EN 0 /* this should be set by AP only when it's ready */
58#define INIT_RESET_TSF 0
59
60/*
61 * Various fifo fill before Tx start, in 64-byte units
62 * i.e. put the frame in the air while still DMAing
63 */
64#define MIN_TX_FIFO_THRESHOLD 0x1
65#define MAX_TX_FIFO_THRESHOLD ((IEEE80211_MAX_LEN / 64) + 1)
66#define INIT_TX_FIFO_THRESHOLD MIN_TX_FIFO_THRESHOLD
67
68/*
69 * Gain support.
70 */
71typedef struct _gainOptStep {
72 int16_t paramVal[4];
73 int32_t stepGain;
74 int8_t stepName[16];
75} GAIN_OPTIMIZATION_STEP;
76
77typedef struct {
78 uint32_t numStepsInLadder;
79 uint32_t defaultStepNum;
80 GAIN_OPTIMIZATION_STEP optStep[10];
81} GAIN_OPTIMIZATION_LADDER;
82
83typedef struct {
84 uint32_t currStepNum;
85 uint32_t currGain;
86 uint32_t targetGain;
87 uint32_t loTrig;
88 uint32_t hiTrig;
89 uint32_t active;
90 const GAIN_OPTIMIZATION_STEP *currStep;
91} GAIN_VALUES;
92
93enum {
94 RFGAIN_INACTIVE,
95 RFGAIN_READ_REQUESTED,
96 RFGAIN_NEED_CHANGE
97};
98
99/*
100 * Header Info - general parameters and
101 * values set for each chipset board solution
102 * that are programmed every reset
103 */
104struct ath_hal_5211 {
105 struct ath_hal_private ah_priv; /* base class */
106
107 GAIN_VALUES ah_gainValues;
108
109 uint8_t ah_macaddr[IEEE80211_ADDR_LEN];
110 uint8_t ah_bssid[IEEE80211_ADDR_LEN];
111
112 /*
113 * Runtime state.
114 */
115 uint32_t ah_maskReg; /* copy of AR_IMR */
116 uint32_t ah_txOkInterruptMask;
117 uint32_t ah_txErrInterruptMask;
118 uint32_t ah_txDescInterruptMask;
119 uint32_t ah_txEolInterruptMask;
120 uint32_t ah_txUrnInterruptMask;
121 HAL_TX_QUEUE_INFO ah_txq[HAL_NUM_TX_QUEUES];
122 HAL_POWER_MODE ah_powerMode;
123 HAL_ANT_SETTING ah_diversityControl; /* antenna setting */
124 uint32_t ah_calibrationTime;
125 HAL_BOOL ah_bIQCalibration;
126 HAL_CHANNEL ah_curchan; /* XXX */
127 int ah_rfgainState;
128 uint32_t ah_tx6PowerInHalfDbm; /* power output for 6Mb tx */
129 uint32_t ah_staId1Defaults; /* STA_ID1 default settings */
130 uint32_t ah_beaconInterval;
131 uint32_t ah_rssiThr; /* RSSI_THR settings */
132
133 u_int ah_sifstime; /* user-specified sifs time */
134 u_int ah_slottime; /* user-specified slot time */
135 u_int ah_acktimeout; /* user-specified ack timeout */
136 u_int ah_ctstimeout; /* user-specified cts timeout */
137 /*
138 * RF Silent handling.
139 */
140 uint32_t ah_gpioSelect; /* GPIO pin to use */
141 uint32_t ah_polarity; /* polarity to disable RF */
142 uint32_t ah_gpioBit; /* after init, prev value */
143};
144#define AH5211(ah) ((struct ath_hal_5211 *)(ah))
